observations.recommendation:
We recommend that the Municipal Mayor and members of the Municipal Development Council (MDC), through the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator:

Avoid lump sum appropriations with generic terms in the Annual Budget and in the Annual Investment Plan; instead, provide details and specific description of the items to be funded and procured;

Secure first the authorization from the Sangguniang Bayan prior to entering into a contract proceeding from lumpsum or generic appropriations.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor issue a directive to all Heads of Offices in the LGU instructing that receipt and deliveries of all procured supplies and materials should be centralized and handled by the Supply Officer only for monitoring and proper recording by the said office.

We also recommended that, in subsequent procurement, the Supply Officer:
Issue a pre-numbered approved Requisition and Issue Slip upon release of any kind of supplies and materials to the end-users;
Prepare the Report of Supplies and Materials Issued (RSMI) duly supported with pre-numbered RIS issued during each month and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant every 1st week of the month to reduce his accountability, and;
Maintain Stock Cards and record all supplies upon receipt of deliveries supported with the Acceptance and Inspection Report.

Further, we recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
Record all supplies in the Inventory account upon purchase;
Record issued supplies in the appropriate expense account based on the  RSMI and RIS from the Supply Officer, and;
Prepare and maintain Supplies Ledger Cards to record receipts, issuances and balances of supplies procured by the LGU. The SLC must be properly posted and kept updated always to support the Inventory account in the books of the LGU.

Lastly, we recommended that the Inventory Committee conduct a complete physical count of all inventory items every end of the year and submit a complete RPCI to the Municipal Accountant for reconciliation with the balances in the Supplies Ledger Card.
